star_ι:
@[simp]
theorem star_ι (x : X) : star (ι R x) = ι R x := by simp [star, has_star.star]
#align star_ι star_ι
star_one:
#print star_one /-
/-- Note that `star_one` is already a global simp lemma, but this one works with dsimp too -/
@[simp]
theorem star_one : star (1 : FreeMonoid α) = 1 :=
  rfl
#align star_one star_one
-/

theorem star_of (x : α) : star (of x) = of x :=

star_algebra_map:
@[simp]
theorem star_algebra_map (r : R) : star (algebra_map R (free_algebra R X) r) = algebra_map R _ r := by
  simp [star, has_star.star]
#align star_algebra_map star_algebra_map
